The paper primarily focuses on investigating the necessity of weight-sharing in computer vision applications, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The study also explores the use of neural circuitry-inspired approaches, which could potentially fall under the categories of neural networks (cs.NE), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and systems and control (cs.SY).
